{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I've got apparently 18 minutes"},{"time":3000,"text":"to convince you that history has a direction, an arrow;"},{"time":6000,"text":"that in some fundamental sense, it's good;"},{"time":9000,"text":"that the arrow points to something positive."},{"time":12000,"text":"Now, when the TED people first approached me about giving this upbeat talk --"},{"time":16000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":17000,"text":"-- that was before the cartoon of Muhammad had triggered global rioting."},{"time":23000,"text":"It was before the avian flu had reached Europe."},{"time":25000,"text":"It was before Hamas had won the Palestinian election,"},{"time":27000,"text":"eliciting various counter-measures by Israel."},{"time":31000,"text":"And to be honest, if I had known when I was asked to give this upbeat talk"},{"time":35000,"text":"that even as I was giving the upbeat talk,"},{"time":38000,"text":"the apocalypse would be unfolding --"},{"time":41000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":42000,"text":"-- I might have said, \"Is it okay if I talk about something else?\""},{"time":46000,"text":"But I didn't, OK. So we're here. I'll do what I can. I'll do what I can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52000,"text":"I've got to warn you:"},{"time":54000,"text":"the sense in which my worldview is upbeat has always been kind of subtle,"},{"time":61000,"text":"sometimes even elusive."},{"time":63000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":64000,"text":"The sense in which I can be uplifting and inspiring --"},{"time":67000,"text":"I mean, there's always been a kind of a certain grim dimension"},{"time":70000,"text":"to the way I try to uplift, so if grim inspiration --"},{"time":74000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":75000,"text":"-- if grim inspiration is not a contradiction in terms, that is, I'm afraid,"},{"time":79000,"text":"the most you can hope for. OK, today -- that's if I succeed."},{"time":83000,"text":"I'll see what I can do. OK?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"Now, in one sense,"},{"time":87000,"text":"the claim that history has a direction is not that controversial."},{"time":90000,"text":"If you're just talking about social structure,"},{"time":93000,"text":"OK, clearly that's gotten more complex"},{"time":95000,"text":"a little over the last 10,000 years -- has reached higher and higher levels."},{"time":98000,"text":"And in fact, that's actually sustaining"},{"time":100000,"text":"a long-standing trend that predates human beings, OK,"},{"time":104000,"text":"that biological evolution was doing for us."},{"time":107000,"text":"Because what happened in the beginning, this stuff encases itself in a cell,"},{"time":112000,"text":"then cells start hanging out together in societies."},{"time":115000,"text":"Eventually they get so close, they form multicellular organisms,"},{"time":118000,"text":"then you get complex multicellular organisms; they form societies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123000,"text":"But then at some point, one of these multicellular organisms"},{"time":126000,"text":"does something completely amazing with this stuff, which is"},{"time":129000,"text":"it launches a whole second kind of evolution: cultural evolution."},{"time":134000,"text":"And amazingly, that evolution sustains the trajectory"},{"time":137000,"text":"that biological evolution had established toward greater complexity."},{"time":142000,"text":"By cultural evolution we mean the evolution of ideas."},{"time":145000,"text":"A lot of you have heard the term \"memes.\" The evolution of technology,"},{"time":148000,"text":"I pay a lot of attention to, so, you know,"},{"time":150000,"text":"one of the first things you got was a little hand axe."},{"time":154000,"text":"Generations go by, somebody says, hey, why don't we put it on a stick?"},{"time":159000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":162000,"text":"Just absolutely delights the little ones."},{"time":165000,"text":"Next best thing to a video game."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"This may not seem to impress,"},{"time":169000,"text":"but technological evolution is progressive, so another 10, 20,000 years,"},{"time":173000,"text":"and armaments technology takes you here."},{"time":175000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":176000,"text":"Impressive. And the rate of technological evolution speeds up,"},{"time":180000,"text":"so a mere quarter of a century after this, you get this, OK."},{"time":184000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":186000,"text":"And this."},{"time":188000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":189000,"text":"I'm sorry -- it was a cheap laugh, but I wanted to find a way"},{"time":192000,"text":"to transition back to this idea of the unfolding apocalypse,"},{"time":195000,"text":"and I thought that might do it."},{"time":197000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":204000,"text":"So, what threatens to happen with this unfolding apocalypse"},{"time":209000,"text":"is the collapse of global social organization."},{"time":213000,"text":"Now, first let me remind you how much work it took to get us where we are,"},{"time":216000,"text":"to be on the brink of true global social organization."},{"time":219000,"text":"Originally, you had the most complex societies, the hunter-gatherer village."},{"time":225000,"text":"Stonehenge is the remnant of a chiefdom,"},{"time":227000,"text":"which is what you get with the invention of agriculture: multi-village polity"},{"time":230000,"text":"with centralized rule."},{"time":233000,"text":"With the invention of writing, you start getting cities. This is blurry. I kind of like that"},{"time":238000,"text":"because it makes it look like a one-celled organism and reminds you"},{"time":241000,"text":"how many levels organic organization has already moved through"},{"time":245000,"text":"to get to this point. And then you get to, you know, you get empires."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251000,"text":"I want to stress, you know, social organization can transcend political bounds."},{"time":255000,"text":"This is the Silk Road connecting the Chinese Empire and the Roman Empire."},{"time":259000,"text":"So you had social complexity spanning the whole continent,"},{"time":262000,"text":"even if no polity did similarly. Today, you've got nation states."},{"time":267000,"text":"Point is: there's obviously collaboration and organization going on"},{"time":270000,"text":"beyond national bounds."},{"time":272000,"text":"This is actually just a picture of the earth at night,"},{"time":275000,"text":"and I'm just putting it up because I think it's pretty."},{"time":277000,"text":"Does kind of convey the sense that this is an integrated system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282000,"text":"Now, I explained this growth of complexity by reference to something"},{"time":288000,"text":"called \"non-zero sumness.\""},{"time":292000,"text":"Assuming that a few of you did not do the assigned reading, very quickly,"},{"time":297000,"text":"the key idea is the distinction between zero-sum games, in which correlations"},{"time":302000,"text":"are inverse: always a winner and a loser."},{"time":305000,"text":"Non-zero-sum games in which correlations can be positive, OK."},{"time":309000,"text":"So like in tennis, usually it's win-lose;"},{"time":313000,"text":"it always adds up to zero-zero-sum. But if you're playing doubles,"},{"time":316000,"text":"the person on your side of the net, they're in the same boat as you,"},{"time":318000,"text":"so you're playing a non-zero-sum game with them."},{"time":320000,"text":"It's either for the better or for the worse, OK."},{"time":323000,"text":"A lot of forms of non-zero-sum behavior in the realm of economics and so on"},{"time":328000,"text":"in everyday life often leads to cooperation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332000,"text":"The argument I make is basically that, well,"},{"time":334000,"text":"non-zero-sum games have always been part of life."},{"time":336000,"text":"You have them in hunter-gatherer societies,"},{"time":338000,"text":"but then through technological evolution, new forms of technology arise"},{"time":343000,"text":"that facilitate or encourage the playing of non-zero-sum games,"},{"time":348000,"text":"involving more people over larger territory."},{"time":351000,"text":"Social structure adapts to accommodate this possibility and"},{"time":355000,"text":"to harness this productive potential, so you get cities, you know,"},{"time":358000,"text":"and you get all the non-zero-sum games you don't think about"},{"time":361000,"text":"that are being played across the world."},{"time":362000,"text":"Like, have you ever thought when you buy a car,"},{"time":365000,"text":"how many people on how many different continents contributed"},{"time":367000,"text":"to the manufacture of that car? Those are people in effect"},{"time":372000,"text":"you're playing a non-zero-sum game with."},{"time":374000,"text":"I mean, there are certainly plenty of them around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381000,"text":"Now, this sounds like an intrinsically upbeat worldview in a way,"},{"time":384000,"text":"because when you think of non-zero, you think win-win, you know,"},{"time":387000,"text":"that's good. Well, there are a few reasons"},{"time":389000,"text":"that actually it's not intrinsically upbeat."},{"time":392000,"text":"First of all, it can accommodate; it doesn't deny the existence"},{"time":396000,"text":"of inequality exploitation war."},{"time":399000,"text":"But there's a more fundamental reason"},{"time":401000,"text":"that it's not intrinsically upbeat, because a non-zero-sum game,"},{"time":404000,"text":"all it tells you for sure is that the fortunes will be correlated for better or worse."},{"time":408000,"text":"It doesn't necessarily predict a win-win outcome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"So, in a way, the question is: on what grounds"},{"time":416000,"text":"am I upbeat at all about history? And the answer is,"},{"time":420000,"text":"first of all, on balance I would say people have played their games"},{"time":424000,"text":"to more win-win outcomes than lose-lose outcomes. On balance,"},{"time":428000,"text":"I think history is a net positive in the non-zero-sum game department."},{"time":434000,"text":"And a testament to this is the thing that most amazes me,"},{"time":439000,"text":"most impresses me, and most uplifts me,"},{"time":441000,"text":"which is that there is a moral dimension to history;"},{"time":446000,"text":"there is a moral arrow. We have seen moral progress over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"2,500 years ago, members of one Greek city-state"},{"time":453000,"text":"considered members of another Greek city-state subhuman"},{"time":456000,"text":"and treated them that way. And then this moral revolution arrived,"},{"time":461000,"text":"and they decided that actually, no, Greeks are human beings."},{"time":465000,"text":"It's just the Persians who aren't fully human"},{"time":468000,"text":"and don't deserve to be treated very nicely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470000,"text":"But this was progress -- you know, give them credit. And now today,"},{"time":473000,"text":"we've seen more progress. I think -- I hope -- most people here would say"},{"time":476000,"text":"that all people everywhere are human beings,"},{"time":479000,"text":"deserve to be treated decently,"},{"time":482000,"text":"unless they do something horrendous, regardless of race or religion."},{"time":486000,"text":"And you have to read your ancient history to realize what a revolution that has been,"},{"time":490000,"text":"OK. This was not a prevalent view,"},{"time":492000,"text":"few thousand years ago, and I attribute it to this non-zero-sum dynamic."},{"time":497000,"text":"I think that's the reason there is as much tolerance toward nationalities,"},{"time":501000,"text":"ethnicities, religions as there is today. If you asked me,"},{"time":506000,"text":"you know, why am I not in favor of bombing Japan,"},{"time":508000,"text":"well, I'm only half-joking when I say they built my car."},{"time":511000,"text":"We have this non-zero-sum relationship,"},{"time":513000,"text":"and I think that does lead to a kind of a tolerance to the extent that you realize"},{"time":519000,"text":"that someone else's welfare is positively correlated with yours --"},{"time":523000,"text":"you're more likely to cut them a break."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525000,"text":"I kind of think this is a kind of a business-class morality."},{"time":530000,"text":"Unfortunately, I don't fly trans-Atlantic business class often enough"},{"time":534000,"text":"to know, or any other kind of business class really,"},{"time":537000,"text":"but I assume that in business class, you don't hear many expressions of, you know,"},{"time":541000,"text":"bigotry about racial groups or ethnic groups,"},{"time":544000,"text":"because the people who are flying trans-Atlantic business class"},{"time":547000,"text":"are doing business with all these people; they're making money"},{"time":549000,"text":"off all these people. And I really do think that, in that sense at least,"},{"time":553000,"text":"capitalism has been a constructive force,"},{"time":556000,"text":"and more fundamentally, it's a non-zero-sumness"},{"time":558000,"text":"that has been a constructive force in expanding people's realm"},{"time":562000,"text":"of moral awareness. I think the non-zero-sum dynamic,"},{"time":567000,"text":"which is not only economic by any means -- it's not always commerce --"},{"time":571000,"text":"but it has driven us to the verge of a moral truth,"},{"time":576000,"text":"which is the fundamental equality of everyone. It has done that."},{"time":579000,"text":"As it has moved global, moved us toward a global level of social organization,"},{"time":584000,"text":"it has driven us toward moral truth."},{"time":586000,"text":"I think that's wonderful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589000,"text":"Now, back to the unfolding apocalypse."},{"time":592000,"text":"And you may wonder, OK, that's all fine,"},{"time":594000,"text":"sounds great -- moral direction in history --"},{"time":596000,"text":"but what about this so-called clash of civilizations? Well, first of all,"},{"time":605000,"text":"I would emphasize that it fits into the non-zero-sum framework,"},{"time":608000,"text":"OK. If you look at the relationship"},{"time":610000,"text":"between the so-called Muslim world and Western world --"},{"time":613000,"text":"two terms I don't like, but can't really avoid;"},{"time":616000,"text":"in such a short span of time, they're efficient if nothing else --"},{"time":620000,"text":"it is non-zero-sum. And by that I mean,"},{"time":623000,"text":"if people in the Muslim world get more hateful, more resentful,"},{"time":627000,"text":"less happy with their place in the world,"},{"time":628000,"text":"it'll be bad for the West. If they get more happy, it'll be good for the West."},{"time":632000,"text":"So that is a non-zero-sum dynamic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637000,"text":"And I would say the non-zero-sum dynamic is only going to grow more intense over time"},{"time":641000,"text":"because of technological trends, but more intense in a kind of negative way."},{"time":646000,"text":"It's the downside correlation of their fortunes that will become more and more possible."},{"time":652000,"text":"And one reason is because of something I call the \"growing lethality of hatred.\""},{"time":657000,"text":"More and more, it's possible for grassroots hatred abroad"},{"time":661000,"text":"to manifest itself in the form of organized violence on American soil."},{"time":666000,"text":"And that's pretty new, and I think it's probably going to get a lot worse"},{"time":669000,"text":"-- this capacity -- because of"},{"time":672000,"text":"trends in information technology, in technologies that can be used"},{"time":676000,"text":"for purposes of munitions like biotechnology and nanotechnology."},{"time":682000,"text":"We may be hearing more about that today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684000,"text":"And there's something I worry about especially, which is that"},{"time":687000,"text":"this dynamic will lead to a kind of a feedback cycle that puts us on a slippery slope."},{"time":693000,"text":"What I have in mind is: terrorism happens here; we overreact to it."},{"time":696000,"text":"That, you know, we're not sufficiently surgical in our retaliation"},{"time":700000,"text":"leads to more hatred abroad, more terrorism."},{"time":702000,"text":"We overreact because being human, we feel like retaliating,"},{"time":706000,"text":"and it gets worse and worse and worse."},{"time":708000,"text":"You could call this the positive feedback of negative vibes,"},{"time":712000,"text":"but I think in something so spooky,"},{"time":714000,"text":"we really shouldn't have the word positive there at all, even in a technical sense."},{"time":717000,"text":"So let's call it the death spiral of negativity."},{"time":720000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":722000,"text":"I assure you if it happens, at the end, both the West"},{"time":724000,"text":"and the Muslim world will have suffered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727000,"text":"So, what do we do? Well, first of all, we can do a lot more with arms control,"},{"time":733000,"text":"the international regulation of dangerous technologies."},{"time":735000,"text":"I have a whole global governance sermon"},{"time":737000,"text":"that I will spare you right now,"},{"time":739000,"text":"because I don't think that's going to be enough anyway, although it's essential."},{"time":742000,"text":"I think we're going to have to have a major round"},{"time":744000,"text":"of moral progress in the world."},{"time":746000,"text":"I think you're just going to have to see less hatred among groups,"},{"time":751000,"text":"less bigotry, and, you know, racial groups, religious groups, whatever."},{"time":757000,"text":"I've got to admit I feel silly saying that."},{"time":759000,"text":"It sounds so kind of Pollyannaish. I feel like Rodney King, you know,"},{"time":762000,"text":"saying, why can't we all just get along?"},{"time":764000,"text":"But hey, I don't really see any alternative, given the way I read the situation."},{"time":770000,"text":"There's going to have to be moral progress."},{"time":773000,"text":"There's going to have to be a lessening of the amount of hatred in the world,"},{"time":777000,"text":"given how dangerous it's becoming."},{"time":781000,"text":"In my defense, I'd say, as naive as this may sound,"},{"time":784000,"text":"it's ultimately grounded in cynicism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787000,"text":"That is to say --"},{"time":788000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":789000,"text":"-- thank you, thank you. That is to say, remember: my whole view"},{"time":794000,"text":"of morality is that it boils down to self-interest."},{"time":797000,"text":"It's when people's fortunes are correlated."},{"time":799000,"text":"It's when your welfare conduces to mine, that I decide, oh yeah,"},{"time":802000,"text":"I'm all in favor of your welfare. That's what's responsible"},{"time":806000,"text":"for this growth of this moral progress so far,"},{"time":809000,"text":"and I'm saying we once again have a correlation of fortunes,"},{"time":812000,"text":"and if people respond to it intelligently, we will see"},{"time":816000,"text":"the development of tolerance and so on --"},{"time":819000,"text":"the norms that we need, you know."},{"time":822000,"text":"We will see the further evolution of this kind of business-class morality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826000,"text":"So, these two things, you know, if they get people's attention"},{"time":832000,"text":"and drive home the positive correlation and people do what's in their self-interests,"},{"time":835000,"text":"which is further the moral evolution,"},{"time":839000,"text":"then they could actually have a constructive effect."},{"time":842000,"text":"And that's why I lump growing lethality of hatred"},{"time":845000,"text":"and death spiral of negativity under the general rubric,"},{"time":848000,"text":"reasons to be cheerful."},{"time":850000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":852000,"text":"Doing the best I can, OK."},{"time":854000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":855000,"text":"I never called myself Mr. Uplift."},{"time":857000,"text":"I'm just doing what I can here."},{"time":860000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":861000,"text":"Now, launching a moral revolution has got to be hard, right?"},{"time":864000,"text":"I mean, what do you do?"},{"time":866000,"text":"And I think the answer is a lot of different people"},{"time":868000,"text":"are going to have to do a lot of different things."},{"time":871000,"text":"We all start where we are. Speaking as an American"},{"time":876000,"text":"who has children whose security 10, 20, 30 years down the road"},{"time":880000,"text":"I worry about -- what I personally want to start out doing"},{"time":883000,"text":"is figuring out why so many people around the world hate us, OK."},{"time":887000,"text":"I think that's a worthy research project myself."},{"time":891000,"text":"I also like it because it's an intrinsically kind of morally redeeming exercise."},{"time":896000,"text":"Because to understand why somebody"},{"time":898000,"text":"in a very different culture does something --"},{"time":900000,"text":"somebody you're kind of viewing as alien,"},{"time":902000,"text":"who's doing things you consider strange"},{"time":904000,"text":"in a culture you consider strange -- to really understand why they do"},{"time":908000,"text":"the things they do is a morally redeeming accomplishment,"},{"time":912000,"text":"because you've got to relate their experience to yours."},{"time":914000,"text":"To really understand it, you've got to say, \"Oh, I get it."},{"time":918000,"text":"So when they feel resentful, it's kind of like"},{"time":920000,"text":"the way I feel resentful when this happens,"},{"time":922000,"text":"and for somewhat the same reasons.\" That's true understanding."},{"time":926000,"text":"And I think that is an expansion of your moral compass when you manage to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":932000,"text":"It's especially hard to do when people hate you, OK,"},{"time":935000,"text":"because you don't really, in a sense, want"},{"time":938000,"text":"to completely understand why people hate you."},{"time":940000,"text":"I mean, you want to hear the reason, but you don't want to be able to relate to it."},{"time":942000,"text":"You don't want it to make sense, right? (Laughter)"},{"time":944000,"text":"You don't want to say, \"Well, yeah, I can kind of understand"},{"time":946000,"text":"how a human being in those circumstances"},{"time":948000,"text":"would hate the country I live in.\" That's not a pleasant thing,"},{"time":951000,"text":"but I think it's something that we're going to have to get used to and"}]},{"cues":[{"time":957000,"text":"work on. Now, I want to stress that to understand, you know --"},{"time":968000,"text":"there are people who don't like this whole business of understanding"},{"time":971000,"text":"the grassroots, the root causes of things; they don't want to know"},{"time":975000,"text":"why people hate us. I want to understand it."},{"time":978000,"text":"The reason you're trying to understand why they hate us,"},{"time":980000,"text":"is to get them to quit hating us. The idea"},{"time":983000,"text":"when you go through this moral exercise of really coming to appreciate"},{"time":987000,"text":"their humanity and better understand them, is part of an effort"},{"time":992000,"text":"to get them to appreciate your humanity in the long run."},{"time":994000,"text":"I think it's the first step toward that. That's the long-term goal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":998000,"text":"There are people who worry about this, and in fact,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"I, myself, apparently, was denounced on national TV"},{"time":1008000,"text":"a couple of nights ago because of an op-ed I'd written."},{"time":1012000,"text":"It was kind of along these lines, and the allegation was"},{"time":1014000,"text":"that I have, quote, \"affection for terrorists.\""},{"time":1018000,"text":"Now, the good news is that the person who said it was Ann Coulter."},{"time":1021000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1023000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1025000,"text":"I mean, if you've got to have an enemy, do make it Ann Coulter."},{"time":1027000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1028000,"text":"But it's not a crazy concern, OK, because understanding behavior"},{"time":1032000,"text":"can lead to a kind of empathy,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"and it can make it a little harder to deliver tough love, and so on."},{"time":1037000,"text":"But I think we're a lot closer to erring on the side of not comprehending"},{"time":1044000,"text":"the situation clearly enough, than in comprehending it so clearly"},{"time":1048000,"text":"that we just can't, you know, get the army out to kill terrorists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051000,"text":"So I'm not really worried about it. So --"},{"time":1054000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1056000,"text":"-- I mean, we're going to have to work on a lot of fronts,"},{"time":1061000,"text":"but if we succeed -- if we succeed -- then once again,"},{"time":1068000,"text":"non-zero-sumness and the recognition of non-zero-sum dynamics"},{"time":1072000,"text":"will have forced us to a higher moral level."},{"time":1076000,"text":"And a kind of saving higher moral level,"},{"time":1081000,"text":"something that kind of literally saves the world."},{"time":1083000,"text":"If you look at the word \"salvation\" in the Bible --"},{"time":1086000,"text":"the Christian usage that we're familiar with --"},{"time":1089000,"text":"saving souls, that people go to heaven -- that's actually a latecomer."},{"time":1092000,"text":"The original meaning of the word \"salvation\" in the Bible is about saving the social system."},{"time":1098000,"text":"\"Yahweh is our Savior\" means \"He has saved the nation of Israel,\""},{"time":1101000,"text":"which at the time, was a pretty high-level social organization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1104000,"text":"Now, social organization has reached the global level, and I guess,"},{"time":1108000,"text":"if there's good news I can say I'm bringing you, it's just that"},{"time":1112000,"text":"all the salvation of the world requires is the intelligent pursuit"},{"time":1118000,"text":"of self-interests in a disciplined and careful way."},{"time":1124000,"text":"It's going to be hard. I say we give it a shot anyway"},{"time":1127000,"text":"because we've just come too far to screw it up now."},{"time":1130000,"text":"Thanks."},{"time":1132000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}